Hilal Browser: add Copy URL button in URL bar next to bookmarks

Adds a dedicated "Copy URL" button inside the URL bar next to the bookmarks/star button.
Clicking this button will copy the active tab's current URL to the system clipboard in a single click.

---

diff --git a/browser/base/content/navigator-toolbox.inc.xhtml b/browser/base/content/navigator-toolbox.inc.xhtml
index e7e94e13a990..5c7a50112555 100644
--- a/browser/base/content/navigator-toolbox.inc.xhtml
+++ b/browser/base/content/navigator-toolbox.inc.xhtml
@@ -440,6 +440,14 @@
               <image id="star-button"
                       class="urlbar-icon"/>
             </hbox>
+            <hbox id="copy-url-button-box"
+                  role="button"
+                  class="urlbar-page-action"
+                  title="Copy URL"
+                  onclick="gHilalBrowser.copyCurrentURL()">
+              <image id="copy-url-button"
+                     class="urlbar-icon"/>
+            </hbox>
           </hbox>
           <html:div class="search-one-offs"
               includecurrentengine="true"
